{
  "Question": "<p>I was attempting to solve an MIT integration bee problem (1) when I misread the integral and wrote (2) instead. </p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_59\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\sqrt{x\\cdot\\sqrt[3]{x\\cdot\\sqrt[4]{x\\cdot\\sqrt[5]{x\\ldots}}}}\\,dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mpadded width=\"+1.7pt\"><msqrt><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u22c5</mo><mroot><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u22c5</mo><mroot><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u22c5</mo><mroot><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mroot></mrow><mn>4</mn></mroot></mrow><mn>3</mn></mroot></mrow></msqrt></mpadded><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_60\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\sqrt{x^{2}\\sqrt{x^{3}\\sqrt{x^{4}\\sqrt{x^{5}\\sqrt{x^{6}\\sqrt{x^{7}\\sqrt{x^% {8}\\ldots}}}}}}}\\,dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mpadded width=\"+1.7pt\"><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>7</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mpadded><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>I was able to solve (1), as the integrand simplifies to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_61\"><math alttext=\"x^{e-2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></semantics></math></span>, however, I'm struggling with solving (2). </p> <p>If we rewrite the roots as powers, we get:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_62\"><math alttext=\"\\int x^{\\frac{2}{2}}\\cdot x^{\\frac{3}{4}}\\cdot x^{\\frac{4}{8}}\\cdot x^{\\frac{5% }{16}}\\ldots\\,dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>\u22c5</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>\u22c5</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msup><mo>\u22c5</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></msup></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mpadded width=\"+1.7pt\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi></mpadded><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>combining the powers we get: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_63\"><math alttext=\"\\int x^{\\frac{2}{2}+\\frac{3}{4}+\\frac{4}{8}+\\frac{5}{16}+\\ldots}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>the exponent is the infinite sum</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_64\"><math alttext=\"\\sum^{\\infty}_{n=1}\\frac{n+1}{2^{n}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span> we can split this into:  <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_65\"><math alttext=\"\\sum^{\\infty}_{n=1}\\frac{n}{2^{n}}+\\sum^{\\infty}_{n=1}\\frac{1}{2^{n}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mi>n</mi><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> The right sum is well known except here the sum begins at <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_66\"><math alttext=\"n=1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>, meaning that the right sum evaluates to 1. Messing around with desmos, the integrand appears to be <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_67\"><math alttext=\"x^{3},x&gt;0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>,</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> implying that (3) converges to 3 and the <span class=\"math-container\"><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_68\"><math alttext=\"\\sum^{\\infty}_{n=1}\\frac{n}{2^{n}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mi>n</mi><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span></span> converges to 2.</p> <p>Which is part I'm struggling with. Any ideas? </p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_68\"><math alttext=\"\\sum^{\\infty}_{n=1}\\frac{n}{2^{n}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mi>n</mi><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></msup></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span></p>",
  "Title": "<span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_58\"><math alttext=\"\\int\\sqrt{x^{2}\\sqrt{x^{3}\\sqrt{x^{4}\\sqrt{x^{5}\\sqrt{x^{6}\\sqrt{x^{7}\\sqrt{x^% {8}\\ldots}}}}}}}\\,dx\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mpadded width=\"+1.7pt\"><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>7</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mrow></msqrt></mpadded><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo rspace=\"0pt\">\ud835\udc51</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
